         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Colonial Botanists office ¶ June 3rd [189]2 ¶ Dear Baron, ¶  ¶ I have just received the specimen you have kindly sent me of Randia spinuligera  ¶ F.v.M ¶ . ¶  It is unfortunate that you had not referr...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">92.06.03</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Frederick Bailey</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Letter press copy book 2, p. 85, Queensland Herbarium, Brisbane.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Colonial Botanists office</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">June 3rd [189]2<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Baron,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have just received the specimen you have kindly sent me of <name key="Randia%20spinuligera%20">Randia spinuligera </name>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">F.v.M</hi>
               </seg>.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B92.07.05, p. 43. The specimen M sent is almost certainly BRI-AQ0125629.</p>
               </note> It is unfortunate that you had not referred to my publications for the same plant I published last year under the name of <name key="Randia%20tuberculosa">Randia tuberculosa</name> and specimens I sent to you among the Bellenden Ker plants n. 29.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M recognised his oversight; see M to W. Thiselton-Dyer, July 1892 (in this edition as 92-07-00).</p>
               </note> I feel sorry that you ignore my work. As colonial Botanist of Queensland it is my duty to collect describe and publish the flora and this I do to the best of my ability, prior to my appointment I cared not who named &amp; described so long as the work was done. I work hard and take a deep interest in my work, but if you will not acknowledge the work I cannot help it — you will remember that few of my plants appear in your Census of Australian plants.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B89.12.03.</p>
               </note> And my work upon the New Guinea handed to me by Sir W MacGregor I have heard nothing about since I sent them on to you a copy of your report<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B89.13.11. </p>
               </note> I think should have reached me long ere this. No one can have a higher opinion of you as a botanist but I dont think you treat me as a friend and fellow worker in the Science</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Yours very truly</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>F M Bailey</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Randia%20spinuligera%20">Randia spinuligera </name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Randia%20tuberculosa">Randia tuberculosa</name>
            </p>
